                        {
                            "defaultConfiguration": {
                                "level": "warning"
                            },
                            "fullDescription": {
                                "text": "Netty is an asynchronous event-driven network application framework for rapid development of maintainable high performance protocol servers & clients. In netty-codec-compression versions 4.1.124.Final and below, and netty-codec versions 4.2.4.Final and below, when supplied with specially crafted input, BrotliDecoder and certain other decompression decoders will allocate a large number of reachable byte buffers, which can lead to denial of service. BrotliDecoder.decompress has no limit in how often it calls pull, decompressing data 64K bytes at a time. The buffers are saved in the output list, and remain reachable until OOM is hit. This is fixed in versions 4.1.125.Final of netty-codec and 4.2.5.Final of netty-codec-compression."
                            },
                            "help": {
                                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2025-58057**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|io.netty:netty-codec|4.1.125.Final|[CVE-2025-58057](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-58057)|\n\nNetty is an asynchronous event-driven network application framework for rapid development of maintainable high performance protocol servers & clients. In netty-codec-compression versions 4.1.124.Final and below, and netty-codec versions 4.2.4.Final and below, when supplied with specially crafted input, BrotliDecoder and certain other decompression decoders will allocate a large number of reachable byte buffers, which can lead to denial of service. BrotliDecoder.decompress has no limit in how often it calls pull, decompressing data 64K bytes at a time. The buffers are saved in the output list, and remain reachable until OOM is hit. This is fixed in versions 4.1.125.Final of netty-codec and 4.2.5.Final of netty-codec-compression.",
                                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-58057\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: io.netty:netty-codec\nFixed Version: 4.1.125.Final\nLink: [CVE-2025-58057](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-58057)\nNetty is an asynchronous event-driven network application framework for rapid development of maintainable high performance protocol servers & clients. In netty-codec-compression versions 4.1.124.Final and below, and netty-codec versions 4.2.4.Final and below, when supplied with specially crafted input, BrotliDecoder and certain other decompression decoders will allocate a large number of reachable byte buffers, which can lead to denial of service. BrotliDecoder.decompress has no limit in how often it calls pull, decompressing data 64K bytes at a time. The buffers are saved in the output list, and remain reachable until OOM is hit. This is fixed in versions 4.1.125.Final of netty-codec and 4.2.5.Final of netty-codec-compression."
                            },
                            "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-58057",
                            "id": "CVE-2025-58057",
                            "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
                            "properties": {
                                "cvssv40_baseScore": 6.9,
                                "cvssv40_vector": "CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N",
                                "precision": "very-high",
                                "security-severity": "5.5",
                                "tags": [
                                    "vulnerability",
                                    "security",
                                    "MEDIUM"
                                ]
                            },
                            "shortDescription": {
                                "text": "netty-codec: netty-codec-compression: Netty's BrotliDecoder is vulnerable to DoS via zip bomb style attack"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "defaultConfiguration": {
                                "level": "error"
                            },
                            "fullDescription": {
                                "text": "Netty is an asynchronous, event-driven network application framework. In versions prior to 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final, Netty incorrectly parses quoted strings in HTTP/1.1 chunked transfer encoding extension values, enabling request smuggling attacks. Versions 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final fix the issue."
                            },
                            "help": {
                                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-33870**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|HIGH|io.netty:netty-codec-http|4.1.132.Final, 4.2.10.Final|[CVE-2026-33870](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-33870)|\n\nNetty is an asynchronous, event-driven network application framework. In versions prior to 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final, Netty incorrectly parses quoted strings in HTTP/1.1 chunked transfer encoding extension values, enabling request smuggling attacks. Versions 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final fix the issue.",
                                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-33870\nSeverity: HIGH\nPackage: io.netty:netty-codec-http\nFixed Version: 4.1.132.Final, 4.2.10.Final\nLink: [CVE-2026-33870](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-33870)\nNetty is an asynchronous, event-driven network application framework. In versions prior to 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final, Netty incorrectly parses quoted strings in HTTP/1.1 chunked transfer encoding extension values, enabling request smuggling attacks. Versions 4.1.132.Final and 4.2.10.Final fix the issue."
                            },
