                            "fullDescription": {
                                "text": "In the Elliptic package 6.5.6 for Node.js, EDDSA signature malleability occurs because there is a missing signature length check, and thus zero-valued bytes can be removed or appended."
                            },
                            "help": {
                                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2024-42459**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|elliptic|6.5.7|[CVE-2024-42459](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-42459)|\n\nIn the Elliptic package 6.5.6 for Node.js, EDDSA signature malleability occurs because there is a missing signature length check, and thus zero-valued bytes can be removed or appended.",
                                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2024-42459\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: elliptic\nFixed Version: 6.5.7\nLink: [CVE-2024-42459](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-42459)\nIn the Elliptic package 6.5.6 for Node.js, EDDSA signature malleability occurs because there is a missing signature length check, and thus zero-valued bytes can be removed or appended."
                            },
