                        },
                        {
                            "defaultConfiguration": {
                                "level": "note"
                            },
                            "fullDescription": {
                                "text": "In the Elliptic package 6.5.6 for Node.js, ECDSA signature malleability occurs because BER-encoded signatures are allowed."
                            },
                            "help": {
                                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2024-42461**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|elliptic|6.5.7|[CVE-2024-42461](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-42461)|\n\nIn the Elliptic package 6.5.6 for Node.js, ECDSA signature malleability occurs because BER-encoded signatures are allowed.",
                                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2024-42461\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: elliptic\nFixed Version: 6.5.7\nLink: [CVE-2024-42461](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-42461)\nIn the Elliptic package 6.5.6 for Node.js, ECDSA signature malleability occurs because BER-encoded signatures are allowed."
                            },
                            "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-42461",
                            "id": "CVE-2024-42461",
                            "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
                            "properties": {
                                "cvssv3_baseScore": 5.3,
                                "cvssv3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:N/A:N",
                                "cvssv40_baseScore": 2.7,
                                "cvssv40_vector": "CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N/E:U",
                                "precision": "very-high",
                                "security-severity": "5.3",
                                "tags": [
                                    "vulnerability",
                                    "security",
                                    "LOW"
                                ]
                            },
                            "shortDescription": {
                                "text": "elliptic: nodejs/elliptic: ECDSA implementation malleability due to BER-enconded signatures being allowed"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "defaultConfiguration": {
                                "level": "note"
                            },
                            "fullDescription": {
                                "text": "The Elliptic package 6.5.7 for Node.js, in its for ECDSA implementation, does not correctly verify valid signatures if the hash contains at least four leading 0 bytes and when the order of the elliptic curve's base point is smaller than the hash, because of an _truncateToN anomaly. This leads to valid signatures being rejected. Legitimate transactions or communications may be incorrectly flagged as invalid."
                            },
                            "help": {
                                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2024-48948**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|elliptic|6.6.0|[CVE-2024-48948](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-48948)|\n\nThe Elliptic package 6.5.7 for Node.js, in its for ECDSA implementation, does not correctly verify valid signatures if the hash contains at least four leading 0 bytes and when the order of the elliptic curve's base point is smaller than the hash, because of an _truncateToN anomaly. This leads to valid signatures being rejected. Legitimate transactions or communications may be incorrectly flagged as invalid.",
                                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2024-48948\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: elliptic\nFixed Version: 6.6.0\nLink: [CVE-2024-48948](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-48948)\nThe Elliptic package 6.5.7 for Node.js, in its for ECDSA implementation, does not correctly verify valid signatures if the hash contains at least four leading 0 bytes and when the order of the elliptic curve's base point is smaller than the hash, because of an _truncateToN anomaly. This leads to valid signatures being rejected. Legitimate transactions or communications may be incorrectly flagged as invalid."
                            },
                            "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-48948",
                            "id": "CVE-2024-48948",
                            "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
                            "properties": {
                                "cvssv3_baseScore": 4.8,
                                "cvssv3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:L",
                                "cvssv40_baseScore": 2.3,
                                "cvssv40_vector": "CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:P/PR:N/UI:P/VC:N/VI:L/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N",
                                "precision": "very-high",
                                "security-severity": "4.8",
                                "tags": [
                                    "vulnerability",
                                    "security",
                                    "LOW"
                                ]
                            },
                            "shortDescription": {
                                "text": "elliptic: ECDSA signature verification error may reject legitimate transactions"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "defaultConfiguration": {
                                "level": "note"
                            },
                            "fullDescription": {
                                "text": "The verify function in lib/elliptic/eddsa/index.js in the Elliptic package before 6.5.6 for Node.js omits \"sig.S().gte(sig.eddsa.curve.n) || sig.S().isNeg()\" validation."
                            },
                            "help": {
                                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2024-48949**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|elliptic|6.5.6|[CVE-2024-48949](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-48949)|\n\nThe verify function in lib/elliptic/eddsa/index.js in the Elliptic package before 6.5.6 for Node.js omits \"sig.S().gte(sig.eddsa.curve.n) || sig.S().isNeg()\" validation.",
                                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2024-48949\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: elliptic\nFixed Version: 6.5.6\nLink: [CVE-2024-48949](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-48949)\nThe verify function in lib/elliptic/eddsa/index.js in the Elliptic package before 6.5.6 for Node.js omits \"sig.S().gte(sig.eddsa.curve.n) || sig.S().isNeg()\" validation."
                            },
                            "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2024-48949",
                            "id": "CVE-2024-48949",
                            "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
                            "properties": {
                                "cvssv3_baseScore": 5.3,
                                "cvssv3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N",
                                "cvssv40_baseScore": 2.7,
                                "cvssv40_vector": "CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N/E:U",
                                "precision": "very-high",
                                "security-severity": "5.3",
                                "tags": [
                                    "vulnerability",
                                    "security",
                                    "LOW"
                                ]
                            },
                            "shortDescription": {
                                "text": "elliptic: Missing Validation in Elliptic's EDDSA Signature Verification"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "defaultConfiguration": {
                                "level": "note"
                            },
                            "fullDescription": {
                                "text": "The ECDSA implementation of the Elliptic package generates incorrect signatures if an interim value of 'k' (as computed based on step 3.2 of  RFC 6979 https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6979 ) has leading zeros and is susceptible to cryptanalysis, which can lead to secret key exposure. This happens, because the byte-length of 'k' is incorrectly computed, resulting in its getting truncated during the computation. Legitimate transactions or communications will be broken as a result.\u00a0Furthermore, due to the nature of the fault, attackers could\u2013under certain conditions\u2013derive the secret key, if they could get their hands on both a faulty signature generated by a vulnerable version of Elliptic and a correct signature for the same inputs.\n\nThis issue affects all known versions of Elliptic (at the time of writing, versions less than or equal to 6.6.1)."
                            },
                            "help": {
                                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2025-14505**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|elliptic||[CVE-2025-14505](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-14505)|\n\nThe ECDSA implementation of the Elliptic package generates incorrect signatures if an interim value of 'k' (as computed based on step 3.2 of  RFC 6979 https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6979 ) has leading zeros and is susceptible to cryptanalysis, which can lead to secret key exposure. This happens, because the byte-length of 'k' is incorrectly computed, resulting in its getting truncated during the computation. Legitimate transactions or communications will be broken as a result.\u00a0Furthermore, due to the nature of the fault, attackers could\u2013under certain conditions\u2013derive the secret key, if they could get their hands on both a faulty signature generated by a vulnerable version of Elliptic and a correct signature for the same inputs.\n\nThis issue affects all known versions of Elliptic (at the time of writing, versions less than or equal to 6.6.1).",
                                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-14505\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: elliptic\nFixed Version: \nLink: [CVE-2025-14505](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-14505)\nThe ECDSA implementation of the Elliptic package generates incorrect signatures if an interim value of 'k' (as computed based on step 3.2 of  RFC 6979 https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6979 ) has leading zeros and is susceptible to cryptanalysis, which can lead to secret key exposure. This happens, because the byte-length of 'k' is incorrectly computed, resulting in its getting truncated during the computation. Legitimate transactions or communications will be broken as a result.\u00a0Furthermore, due to the nature of the fault, attackers could\u2013under certain conditions\u2013derive the secret key, if they could get their hands on both a faulty signature generated by a vulnerable version of Elliptic and a correct signature for the same inputs.\n\nThis issue affects all known versions of Elliptic (at the time of writing, versions less than or equal to 6.6.1)."
                            },
                            "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-14505",
                            "id": "CVE-2025-14505",
                            "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
                            "properties": {
                                "cvssv3_baseScore": 5.6,
                                "cvssv3_vector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:L",
                                "cvssv40_baseScore": 2.9,
                                "cvssv40_vector": "CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:P/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N/E:P",
                                "precision": "very-high",
                                "security-severity": "5.6",
                                "tags": [
