                        {
                            "defaultConfiguration": {
                                "level": "warning"
                            },
                            "fullDescription": {
                                "text": "Serialize JavaScript to a superset of JSON that includes regular expressions and functions. Prior to version 7.0.5, there is a Denial of Service (DoS) vulnerability caused by CPU exhaustion. When serializing a specially crafted \"array-like\" object (an object that inherits from Array.prototype but has a very large length property), the process enters an intensive loop that consumes 100% CPU and hangs indefinitely. This issue has been patched in version 7.0.5."
                            },
                            "help": {
                                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-34043**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|serialize-javascript|7.0.5|[CVE-2026-34043](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-34043)|\n\nSerialize JavaScript to a superset of JSON that includes regular expressions and functions. Prior to version 7.0.5, there is a Denial of Service (DoS) vulnerability caused by CPU exhaustion. When serializing a specially crafted \"array-like\" object (an object that inherits from Array.prototype but has a very large length property), the process enters an intensive loop that consumes 100% CPU and hangs indefinitely. This issue has been patched in version 7.0.5.",
                                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-34043\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: serialize-javascript\nFixed Version: 7.0.5\nLink: [CVE-2026-34043](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-34043)\nSerialize JavaScript to a superset of JSON that includes regular expressions and functions. Prior to version 7.0.5, there is a Denial of Service (DoS) vulnerability caused by CPU exhaustion. When serializing a specially crafted \"array-like\" object (an object that inherits from Array.prototype but has a very large length property), the process enters an intensive loop that consumes 100% CPU and hangs indefinitely. This issue has been patched in version 7.0.5."
                            },
                            "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-34043",
                            "id": "CVE-2026-34043",
                            "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
                            "properties": {
