                        {
                            "defaultConfiguration": {
                                "level": "note"
                            },
                            "fullDescription": {
                                "text": "tmp is a temporary file and directory creator for node.js. In versions 0.2.3 and below, tmp is vulnerable to an arbitrary temporary file / directory write via symbolic link dir parameter. This is fixed in version 0.2.4."
                            },
                            "help": {
                                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2025-54798**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|LOW|tmp|0.2.4|[CVE-2025-54798](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-54798)|\n\ntmp is a temporary file and directory creator for node.js. In versions 0.2.3 and below, tmp is vulnerable to an arbitrary temporary file / directory write via symbolic link dir parameter. This is fixed in version 0.2.4.",
                                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2025-54798\nSeverity: LOW\nPackage: tmp\nFixed Version: 0.2.4\nLink: [CVE-2025-54798](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2025-54798)\ntmp is a temporary file and directory creator for node.js. In versions 0.2.3 and below, tmp is vulnerable to an arbitrary temporary file / directory write via symbolic link dir parameter. This is fixed in version 0.2.4."
                            },
